Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Trim the @pak choi{1}, then separate the leaves. Cut any large leaves in half
lengthways down the middle.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and green beans. Fry until the
mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a
#rolling pin{}.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pak choi and garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @gochujang paste{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @honey{1%tbsp} and
@water{50%ml} to the pan.

> Add less gochujang paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil and simmer until slightly reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%g} to the pan.

Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer until piping
hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share the gochujang pork noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the crushed peanuts to finish. Enjoy!